body:
@theStack, @mzumsande thank you for the reviews! I've rebased and addressed your comments.

> It seems like the newly introduced functional test p2p_v2_encrypted.py could be merged with the already existing p2p_v2_transport.py (here or in a follow-up), or is it fundamentally different?

yes! can be done in a follow up. only difference is `p2p_v2_encrypted.py` tests `TestNode` <--> `P2PInterface` behaviour and `p2p_v2_transport.py` tests `TestNode` <--> `TestNode` behaviour. So maybe in separate functions within `p2p_v2_transport.py`?

@maflcko, I still need to address the CI failure. https://api.cirrus-ci.com/v1/task/6171895557521408/logs/ci.log

In commit "[test] Construct class to handle v2 P2P protocol functions"

This needs to be `return processed_length, True`, as there may be been decoys before (I can trigger a failure in p2p_v2_encrypted.py by making Bitcoin Core send large decoys before the version packet). <details><summary>Code to trigger it:</summary>
```diff
--- a/src/net.cpp
+++ b/src/net.cpp
@@ -1130,6 +1130,15 @@ bool V2Transport::ProcessReceivedKeyBytes() noexcept
                   m_cipher.GetSendGarbageTerminator().end(),
                   MakeWritableByteSpan(m_send_buffer).last(BIP324Cipher::GARBAGE_TERMINATOR_LEN).begin());
 
+        unsigned decoys = GetRand<unsigned>(10);
+        while (decoys--) {
+            unsigned decoysize = GetRand<unsigned>(4000000);
+            m_send_buffer.resize(m_send_buffer.size() + BIP324Cipher::EXPANSION + decoysize);
+            std::vector<std::byte> decoy_data(decoysize);
+            m_cipher.Encrypt(decoy_data, MakeByteSpan(m_send_garbage), true, MakeWritableByteSpan(m_send_buffer).last(BIP324Cipher::EXPANSION + decoysize));
+            ClearShrink(m_send_garbage);
+        }
+
         // Construct version packet in the send buffer, with the sent garbage data as AAD.
```
</details>

I think it would be even cleaner to change `v2_receive_packet` to also return `contents = None` in case no complete packet was received. In that case, the whole `elif length == 0:` branch can go away.
